marked: In the present study, we report about qualitative and quantitative volumetric brain differences derived from structural MR imaging, focusing on lateral temporal and parietal lobe structures that might guide as neuromorphometric biomarkers for distinguishing between health, MCI, and probable late onset AD.
Memory functions were assessed with subtests from the Wechsler Memory Scale-Revised in German
Spatial thinking was assessed with the Luria Mental Rotation Test
